name: FLYING AIR INUIT'S BOEING 737-200 COMBI! Montreal to Puvirnituq (4K)
description:
Canada has 5 operators who fly the Boeing 737-200, although only two of them fly commercial scheduled flights. I've flown on Canadian North's a number of times, and when the opportunity came up to take a flight with Air Inuit's 737-200, I knew I had to take it!

Special thank you to the person who made this possible.

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Airline: Air Inuit (AIE/3H)
Aircraft: Boeing 737-200 Combi (B732)
Flight Number: 3H700
Seat: 16A
Livery: Standard
Engines: 2x Pratt and Whitney JT8D-9A 
Registration: C-GSPW
Route: Montreal (YUL) - Puvirnituq (YPX)
Callsign: AIR INUIT 700
Runway used: 06R (YUL) - 19 (YPX)
Date filmed: August 2021
